flowRoot.flowPara: Use Photos to manage a collection taken with one or more cameras.
Do as much automatically as possible - take over the work of "managing" files from the user.

The first time a device is discovered that contains images, the user is asked if they want to import them, using an in-app notification (or a regular notification, if Photos isn't running). The in-app notification should be displayed in Photos while the device is present (irrespective of whether the regular notification has been dismissed).
Placeholder thumbnails are shown for the images, which are filled in as they are imported.
Once a device has been used as an image source, it is scanned for new images if it reappears. Notifications allow new images to be imported.
Optimise for cameras "connected" using SD cards, USB or a WiFi connection. Assume that the entire collection of images from these devices will be managed by Photos.
The goal is typically to share images or prepare a device for use - import shouldn't get in the way, or be a nuisance.
